    <section id="faq" class="faq">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p>Common questions about Georgia dealer licensing and training</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-container">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>What is required to get a Georgia used car dealer license?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>To obtain a Georgia used car dealer license, you must:</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>Complete a mandatory 4-hour pre-license educational seminar from a state-approved provider</li>
                            <li>Have a properly zoned location for your dealership with appropriate signage</li>
                            <li>Obtain a $35,000 surety bond</li>
                            <li>Secure garage liability insurance</li>
                            <li>Pass a fingerprint background check</li>
                            <li>Complete and submit the dealer license application with all required documentation</li>
                            <li>Pay the application fee</li>
                            <li>Pass a location inspection</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>How long does it take to get a Georgia dealer license?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The process typically takes 4-8 weeks from the time you submit a complete application. This includes time for the background check, processing of your application, and scheduling of your location inspection. Delays can occur if your application is incomplete or if issues are found during the inspection.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>How much does it cost to get a Georgia dealer license?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The total cost typically ranges from $1,000 to $1,500, which includes:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Pre-license class fee: $195-$250</li>
                            <li>License application fee: Approximately $200</li>
                            <li>Surety bond: $350-$500 (depending on your credit)</li>
                            <li>Garage liability insurance: $300-$600 (varies by location and coverage)</li>
                            <li>Fingerprinting fee: Approximately $50</li>
                            <li>Business license and other local fees: Varies by location</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>Can I operate a dealership from my home in Georgia?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>In some cases, yes. Georgia allows dealers to operate from a residential address if local zoning ordinances permit it. The office must be in a separate building that is detached from the residence, and you must meet all other requirements including proper signage. Urban areas typically have stricter zoning restrictions than rural areas. You must submit a notarized zoning certification from your local zoning authority with your application.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>How often do I need to renew my Georgia dealer license?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Georgia dealer licenses must be renewed every two years, by September 30th of even-numbered years. To renew, you must complete 6 hours of continuing education between January and September of the renewal year. You'll also need to maintain your surety bond and garage liability insurance, and pay the renewal fee.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>Do I need to attend a pre-license class if I'm buying an existing dealership?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes. Even if you're purchasing an existing dealership, if you personally have never held a Georgia dealer license before, you must complete the mandatory 4-hour pre-license educational seminar. The license is issued to the individual or entity applying, not to the physical location.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>What's the difference between a retail and wholesale dealer license in Georgia?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>A retail dealer license allows you to sell vehicles to both consumers and other dealers. A wholesale license only permits sales to other licensed dealers, not to the general public. Both require the same pre-license education, but a wholesale license may have somewhat different location requirements. Most providers cover both types in their pre-license classes.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        <h3>What should I look for when choosing a dealer license class?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>When selecting a dealer license class, consider these important factors:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Class size (smaller classes allow for more personalized attention and questions)</li>
                            <li>Instructor experience and teaching style</li>
                            <li>Logical organization and flow of content</li>
                            <li>Additional services offered (bonds, insurance, consulting)</li>
                            <li>Quality and usefulness of provided materials</li>
                            <li>Post-class support and resources</li>
                            <li>Convenience of location and scheduling</li>
                            <li>Reviews from previous students</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
